{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_278275390ffe4QSZSpoXPeUldX","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d87d8d18e001WryQi4TjYBdgdc","parts":[{"id":"prt_d87d8d931001ein22mxx1kMBaR","messageID":"msg_d87d8d18e001WryQi4TjYBdgdc","sessionID":"ses_278275390ffe4QSZSpoXPeUldX","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_07dee8d4163f48f7ae1250cf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/install.rst"},"output":"<path>/workspace/docs/install.rst</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: Install\n2: =======\n3: \n4: In your project\n5: ---------------\n6: \n7: Install version 3 with :pip:ref:`pip install`::\n8: \n9:     pip install django-autocomplete-light\n10: \n11: Or, install the dev version with git::\n12: \n13:     pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n14: \n15: .. note::\n16:    If you are trying to install from git, please make sure you are not using\n17:    **zip/archive** url of the repo ``django-autocomplete-light`` since it will not\n18:    contain required submodules automatically. Otherwise these submodules will then\n19:    need to be updated separately using ``git submodule update --init``.\n20: \n21: Configuration\n22: -------------\n23: Then, to let Django find the static files we need by adding to\n24: :django:setting:`INSTALLED_APPS`, **before** ``django.contrib.admin`` and\n25: ``grappelli`` if present::\n26: \n27:     'dal',\n28:     'dal_select2',\n29:     # 'grappelli',\n30:     'django.contrib.admin',\n31: \n32: This is to override the ``jquery.init.js`` script provided by the admin, which\n33: sets up jQuery with ``noConflict``, making jQuery available in\n34: ``django.jQuery`` only and not ``$``.\n35: \n36: To enable more DAL functionalities we will have to add other DAL apps\n37: to :django:setting:`INSTALLED_APPS`, such as 'dal_queryset_sequence' ...\n38: \n39: Django versions earlier than 2.0\n40: ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n41: You will need to add dal_legacy_static to your INSTALLED_APPS settings.\n42: This adds in select2 static files that are included with Django 2.x but\n43: missing in earlier versions.\n44: \n45: JQuery 3.x\n46: ^^^^^^^^^^\n47: JQuery 3.x comes with a \"slim\" version. This \"slim\" version is not compatible with\n48: DAL since the slim version does not contain Ajax functionality.\n49: \n50: .. _demo-install:\n51: \n52: Install the demo project\n53: ------------------------\n54: \n55: Install the demo project in a temporary virtualenv for testing purpose::\n56: \n57:     cd /tmp\n58:     virtualenv -p python3 dal_env\n59:     source dal_env/bin/activate\n60:     pip install django\n61:     pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n62:     cd dal_env/src/django-autocomplete-light/test_project/\n63:     pip install -r requirements.txt\n64:     ./manage.py migrate\n65:     ./manage.py createsuperuser\n66:     ./manage.py runserver\n67:     # go to http://localhost:8000/admin/ and login\n\n(End of file - total 67 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Install\n=======\n\nIn your project\n---------------\n\nInstall version 3 with :pip:ref:`pip install`::\n\n    pip install django-autocomplete-light\n\nOr, install the dev version with git::\n\n    pip install -e git+https://github.com/yourlabs/django-autocomplete-light.git#egg=django-autocomplete-light\n\n.. note::\n   If you are trying to install from git, please make sure you are not using\n   **zip/archive** url of the repo ``django-autocomplete-light`` since it will not\n   contain required submodules automatically. Otherwise these submodules will then\n   need to be updated separately using ``git submodule update --init``.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"docs/install.rst","time":{"start":1776100629080,"end":1776100629084}}}]}
